        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 10:01PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1000 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marseilles, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marseilles and Seneca.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
